Reasoning: The paper focuses on using deep learning techniques for feature representation and prediction modeling in the context of Electronic Health Records (EHR). This falls under the broad category of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The use of word embedding techniques also suggests a natural language processing (NLP) component, which could place the paper under the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper deals with issues of data privacy and security in EHRs, which could potentially fall under the sub-categories of cybersecurity (cs.CY) or cryptography (cs.CR).
